  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nFor drop-in replacement of Geth, it'd be useful if both the RPC and WS endpoints for the engine API were on the same port, namely 8551.\r\n\r\nCurrently RPC is on 8550 and WS on 8551:\r\n\r\n```\r\nexecution_1             | 2022-03-21 19:40:11.328+00:00 | vert.x-eventloop-thread-1 | INFO  | JsonRpcHttpService | JSON-RPC service started and listening on 0.0.0.0:8550\r\nexecution_1             | 2022-03-21 19:40:11.330+00:00 | main | INFO  | WebSocketService | Starting Websocket service on 0.0.0.0:8546\r\nexecution_1             | 2022-03-21 19:40:11.337+00:00 | vert.x-eventloop-thread-1 | INFO  | WebSocketService | Websocket service started and listening on 0.0.0.0:8546\r\nexecution_1             | 2022-03-21 19:40:11.338+00:00 | main | INFO  | WebSocketService | Starting Websocket service on 0.0.0.0:8551\r\nexecution_1             | 2022-03-21 19:40:11.340+00:00 | vert.x-eventloop-thread-1 | INFO  | WebSocketService | Websocket service started and listening on 0.0.0.0:8551\r\n```\r\n\r\nGeth, Erigon and Nethermind have a combined RPC/WS endpoint defaulting to 8551.\r\n",
