    "body": "So the \"correct\" way of doing WS is to have a lone, single port, and then either you do get `Connection: Upgrade`, which means it's now a Websocket connection, or you don't, in which case it remains an RPC connection.\r\n\r\nThe initial Geth-ism of having 8545 and 8546 is, to put it mildly, \"odd\". I am glad to see this was ditched for the Engine API and execution layer clients now default to authenticated connections on 8551, deciding on RPC or WS depending on whether the connection was upgraded. See also https://sookocheff.com/post/networking/how-do-websockets-work/\r\n",
